This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image analysis and segmentation. The use of deep learning and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of Medical Segmentation Decathlon Spleen dataset suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
